cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses improving the generalization of deep networks through normalization techniques, which is a common topic in machine learning and specifically in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses image segmentation and machine translation, which are sub-fields of computer vision and natural language processing, respectively, leading to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new normalization technique, which is related to optimization and training of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
